com.iota.iri.service.transactionpruning.jobs

Class MilestonePrunerJob

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iota.iri.service.transactionpruning.jobs.AbstractTransactionPrunerJob
      • com.iota.iri.service.transactionpruning.jobs.MilestonePrunerJob
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TransactionPrunerJob

    public class MilestonePrunerJob
extends AbstractTransactionPrunerJob
    Represents a cleanup job for TransactionPruners that removes milestones and all of their directly and indirectly referenced transactions (and the orphaned subtangles branching off of the deleted transactions). It is used by the LocalSnapshotManager to clean up milestones prior to a snapshot. Even though it defines a range of milestones that shall be deleted, it gets processed one milestone at a time, persisting the progress after each step.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MilestonePrunerJob

        public MilestonePrunerJob(int startingIndex,
                          int targetIndex)
        Does same as MilestonePrunerJob(int, int, int) but defaults to the currentIndex being the same as the startingIndex. This is usually the case when we create a NEW job programmatically that does not get restored from a state file, because we start cleaning up at the startingIndex.
        Parameters:
        startingIndex - milestone index that defines where to start cleaning up

    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public static MilestonePrunerJob parse(java.lang.String input)
                                throws TransactionPruningException
        This method parses the string representation of a MilestonePrunerJob and creates the corresponding object. It splits the String input in three parts (delimited by a ";") and passes them into the constructor of a new MilestonePrunerJob by interpreting them as startingIndex, currentIndex and targetIndex of the job.
        Parameters:
        input - serialized String representation of a MilestonePrunerJob
        Returns:
        a new MilestonePrunerJob with the provided details
        Throws:
        TransactionPruningException - if the string can not be parsed

      • process

        public void process()
             throws TransactionPruningException
        This method processes the cleanup job and performs the actual pruning. It iterates from the currentIndex to the provided targetIndex and processes every milestone one by one. After each step is finished we persist the progress to be able to continue with the current progress upon IRI restarts.
        Specified by:
        process in interface TransactionPrunerJob
        Specified by:
        process in class AbstractTransactionPrunerJob
        Throws:
        TransactionPruningException - if something goes wrong while processing the job

      • serialize

        public java.lang.String serialize()
        This method is used to serialize the job before it gets persisted by the TransactionPruner. It simply concatenates the startingIndex and the currentIndex as they are necessary to fully describe the job.
        Specified by:
        serialize in interface TransactionPrunerJob
